input: Objective: End the process of editing a document
output:
To end the process of editing a document, follow these steps:

1. Save your work by clicking on the "File" menu.
2. Select "Save As..." from the drop-down menu.
3. Choose the location where you want to save your document and enter a file name.
4. Click "Save."
5. Close the document editor. You can do this by clicking the "X" button in the upper right corner of the window, or by selecting "File" > "Close" from the menu bar.
6. If you need to end the process immediately, you can force quit the application. This will close all open documents and save any unsaved changes if prompted.
